Quote: One of the simplest was for the catching firm [deer catchers] or the farmer on whose property the deer happened to be, to build a capture paddock, perhaps in a suitable mountain valley. The helicopter then 'rounded up' the deer and drove as many as possible of them into the capture paddock.
